reviews.name: Nix Kiff
reviews.text:
If only I could give 0 stars, but such an option is not available. Extremely disappointed with the service provided by this dental clinic, particularly with Dr. Goh. Despite the positive reviews given by many, the experience was far from satisfactory. Dr. Goh made commitments regarding the completion of a crown within two sessions, only to change the plan abruptly to require three sessions, causing considerable inconvenience given the time constraints and urgent need to work overseas which have been explained to her repeatedly.

Despite the request for an explanation, Dr. Goh failed to provide one personally, relying instead on the customer service team to address her mistake. This lack of accountability only intensified the situation, highlighting her insincerity.

She only made the helpful people from the customer service team to front her mistake made. Would strongly advise against seeking dental care from this clinic and waste your money especially so if you're rushing for time. And especially not an appointment with Dr. Goh.

reviews.name: Rashmika
reviews.text:
I had an amazing experience with Dr Ashwin and Dr Sho! I consulted them regarding my discolored teeth and expressed that it had been one of my biggest insecurities. They were incredibly attentive, patiently listening to all my concerns and clearly explaining the various whitening options available to me.

They took the time to answer all my questions, ensuring I felt comfortable and informed before moving forward with any treatment.

Once I felt confident in the plan, we proceeded with the procedure, which took about 90 minutes. Throughout the process, Dr. Sho was professional and thorough, and the dental assistants were highly efficient, providing excellent support. The whole team made sure I was at ease, and the entire experience was smooth and stress-free.

I am so pleased with the results and couldnâ€™t be happier with the level of care and expertise provided. I highly recommend Dr. Ashwin and Dr. Sho to anyone looking for top-notch dental care.

My wife and me recently had a root canal treatment and dental crown  by Dr Ashwin at â€˜Klinik Pergigian Rakyat Dental, Perlingâ€™, and I was satisfied with the experience.
He was extremely patient and took the time to explain every step of the procedure, which really helped ease my nerves. His professionalism and gentle approach made the entire process smooth and surprisingly painless.

The staff was also very friendly and welcoming, making the overall experience even better. I truly appreciate the care and attention Dr. Ashwin provided, and I highly recommend him to anyone in need of dental treatment.

reviews.name: Cheiro Theorem
reviews.text:
Iâ€™m glad I found an experienced dentist who was able to identify my oral issues when many others couldnâ€™t. Whenever I went for scaling and polishing, most dentists would tell me my teeth were very clean. Such comments felt like a taboo to me because there are always hidden or hard-to-reach areas that a toothbrush can't properly clean.
Today, my teeth feel incredibly clean. Before starting the procedure, Dr. Ng mentioned that her scaling might be more painful compared to other dentists. She repeatedly confirmed that I was okay with it before proceeding. Her treatment focused not on surface cleaning but on deep cleaning.
Itâ€™s rare to find such a dentist nowadays because many people are afraid of pain, so most dentists choose to focus only on surface cleaning to minimize discomfort. This approach is highly personal. If you value deep cleaning, Dr. Ng is absolutely the right choice. However, if you are pain sensitive, I wouldnâ€™t recommend visiting her, as your gums may need 2-3 days to recover after the procedure.

reviews.name: #Wanderluster
reviews.text:
Made an appointment for scaling and polishing at RM99, WhatsApp booking was easy, responsive and fuss free (I even managed to get an appointment slot for the same day). The clinic is very nicely done up, feels relaxing sitting and waiting for my turn and I didnâ€™t have to wait long after the registration process to be called into the treatment room.

Dr Yew was assigned to me and her services were excellent. She was warm and inviting (I somehow always have this terrible fear of dentists) and that helped a lot with my anxiety. She then proceeded to do a check of my teeth and found that two fillings were worn out and showed some signs of initial decay, taking photos of the affected areas and spending the time and effort to explain the situation. During the treatment she constantly checked in if I was ok, and was very understanding towards my fears / low pain threshold.

In the end, I spent a total of RM439 on two posterior tooth fillings (RM140 each), a scaling and polishing (RM99 as advertised) and an air polishing (RM60) as I had dark tea stains in between teeth that normal polishing were unable to remove. Dr Yew also showed me the after photos of my teeth and I was pleasantly surprised with the results. Would recommend this dental clinic to anyone looking for affordable yet professional dental services - personally I will also be back.

reviews.name: Tan Alicia
reviews.text:
Subject: Lack of Communication and Unprofessional Conduct at IMC Dental (City Square Branch)

Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to formally express my dissatisfaction and disappointment regarding the recent experience I had at your City Square branch. I have been a loyal and regular client of IMC Dental and have introduced several new customers to your clinic over the years. However, the treatment I received during my recent interaction was unacceptable and deeply concerning.

Due to illness, I was unable to attend a scheduled appointment. While I acknowledge the importance of honoring appointments, I was genuinely unwell and resting at home, and unfortunately, it slipped my mind. I was prepared to provide a medical certificate to explain my absence, yet this was dismissed without consideration.

I was met with rudeness from the front desk and from Dr. B, who claimed that missing the appointment was â€œdisrespectfulâ€ as I had been given a priority slot. However, I was never informed that my appointment held such status â€” it was simply scheduled based on the availability provided. Furthermore, I was told I would only be accepted as a walk-in going forward, which contradicts the clinicâ€™s usual practice of not accommodating walk-ins.

This situation clearly reflects a breakdown in communication and a lack of empathy. I felt unfairly blamed and disrespected, despite being a long-term client. The response from your staff showed no flexibility or professionalism and left me extremely disappointed.

Customers have the right to reschedule appointments for valid reasons, including illness and work commitments. I expected more from a clinic I have supported for so long, and I am disappointed that my loyalty was disregarded.

I request that this matter be investigated and addressed accordingly. I hope IMC Dental will take the necessary steps to improve its communication practices and ensure all clients are treated with respect and understanding.

I look forward to your response and a fair resolution to this issue.

Sincerely,

reviews.name: Botak
reviews.text:
Was recommended to Dr Wong by a friend, and I came to do a partial denture.  So when I drove from Woodlands causeway,  it took about 20 minutes, and as long as u made an appointment and arrived on time,  there was no wait at the clinic. But you needed to exchange your shoes for their indoor slippers at the entrance. Though parking could be quite difficult to find if your appointment was in the afternoons.

Interestingly,  unlike in SG, where you needed to do an x-ray and have a thorough check before the dentist would proceed with the procedure,  here there was no x-ray required here, and the doctor would take your word and went on to give you what you wanted.  So, in my case,  since it was to fill up some parts of my teeth with partial dentures,  my existing or new cavities were not addressed. It was only looked into when I asked about it on my 2nd visit to fit the denture.

In any case, the partial denture was fitted in nicely, and I'm pleased with it. I'm not sure about the price as I did not compare it to other clinics,  but it seemed reasonable at RM1700 (Uploaded the price list in my review)

reviews.name: Ryan
reviews.text:
I underwent orthodontic treatment several years ago. Unfortunately, the dentist who treated me acted very unethically. After my orthodontic treatment was completed, she insisted on selling me additional, unnecessary procedures to "enlarge" four of my front teeth. She even suggested replacing my perfectly healthy teeth with crowns for purely aesthetic reasons.

Back then, I didnâ€™t know what a crown was (I was 23 y/o at the time), and when I asked her if the procedure would cost extra, she blatantly lied to me and said no. By the time it was too lateâ€”when my teeth had already been filed down and fitted with temporary crownsâ€”I was slapped with a hefty bill for the crowns!

This happened back in 2016, and Iâ€™m leaving this review today because not a single day goes by without me regretting replacing my completely healthy teeth with crowns at this clinic. The dentist didnâ€™t explain what the procedure would entail, and now Iâ€™m stuck with this decision for the rest of my life, ruining my teeth in the long term.

reviews.name: S.K & SONS EMPIRE
reviews.text:
Subject: Formal Complaint Regarding Dental Treatment and Service Experience

To Prodental Specialists Group,

I am writing to express my deep dissatisfaction and disappointment regarding the treatment and service I have received at your clinic.

When I first visited your clinic, I came prepared with a referral letter and X-rays from another clinic. My main concern was to get braces, and I was hoping for a clear treatment plan and guidance. However, I was advised by Dr. [Name] to begin by treating my gum disease before proceeding with braces. Trusting your expertise, I followed the recommendation and began the treatment.

To date, I have spent over $4,000 and several months undergoing treatment, only to be told recently that I will need to wait another four months before a final decision can be made regarding braces. Whatâ€™s more distressing is that during a consultation with the braces specialist, I was informed that the estimated cost of the full procedureâ€”including retainers, consultations, scaling, and X-raysâ€”would be approximately $20,000 to $25,000.

Had this information been shared with me at the beginningâ€”especially by the braces specialistâ€”I would have had the opportunity to consider all my options, whether to continue treatment with your clinic or seek more affordable alternatives elsewhere. Despite the high cost, I chose to proceed because I trusted that I would receive professional care and see positive results. Unfortunately, that has not been the case.

I want to make it clear that I have all recordings, videos, and receipts from day one until today as documentation of my entire experience. This situation has not only affected me financially but also caused me significant emotional stress. I feel misled and extremely disappointed.

I hope you take this matter seriously and provide a clear explanation and resolution. If this issue is not addressed appropriately, I will have no choice but to consider further action.

Sincerely,
Kayalvizhi Amurthalingam

reviews.text:
In 2018, me and my mum first visited Dr. Jolene's clinic where she assisted my mother on a family complex tooth issue, and after 3-4ish visits over the span of 7 years (the latest visit being last Friday), it's awesome that Dr. Jolene is still as kind, courteous, patient & caring as always. ğŸ¥°ğŸ’› She has definitely been a blessing in our lives (and to our tooth/teeth ğŸ¦·) and the majority of her staff are always polite and helpful as always. Dr. Jolene is, first and foremost, a polite and extremely transparent doctor. I appreciate the fact she's honest with her patients (as I think, in this day and age, that's a rare thing to find) & she isn't pushy about anything either. She's someone who truly puts in care in both her patients and clinic. And honestly, I'm looking forward to my next extraction because of the good experience(s) I had. I do believe it's because she understands my situation and takes extra care/time to make sure I'm doing okay (and gives me time to close my mouth or so if I need to).

I appreciated her telling me to rest a bit when she saw me closing my jaw a little; it was a small yet impressionable gesture which I genuinely appreciated. :) I thank her nurses for being attentive and accommodating too!

I think when you come across a clinic that not only looks good, but is well maintained and has staff that's been there a long time & most are still as bubbly, you can kinda guess the person running has their heart in their practice & doing their best. ğŸ’— My mum and I are grateful to have found Pink & White Dental for sure. Looking forward to seeing Dr. Jolene again! God bless always!

reviews.name: Kai
reviews.text:
I visited Asiaa Dental Clinic yesterday for a teeth whitening session, along with scaling, polishing, and an additional tooth filing procedure. My friend recommended me as she was quite pleased with their treatment. I was attended to by Dr Thasha, and I must sayâ€”Iâ€™m thoroughly impressed with both her and the teamâ€™s overall service and attitude.

Dr Thasha was patient and attentive, clearly explaining each step of the procedures beforehand. Throughout the session, she and the staff consistently checked in to ensure I was comfortable and doing well.

During the second stage of the whitening treatment, I experienced an unexpected reactionâ€”intense numbness and a burning sensation on my lips, which left me panicking as it was something Iâ€™d never felt before. The staff responded immediately, informing Dr Thasha, who attended to me promptly. She remained calm and professional, reassuring me that some patients may have such reactions when the lips come into contact with the chemical. She also explained that the severity of the reaction can vary between individuals. My lips were visibly swollen and appeared burned by the end of the session, but Dr Thasha comforted me that it will disappear after 1-2 days and reduced the duration for the final stage of the treatment to prevent further discomfort. She also told me to contact them if the condition doesn't improve.

Unfortunately, shortly after the session, I experienced sudden and intense sharp pain in the bottom front row of my teeth. Dr Thasha checked in on me, and I informed her about the pain. She kindly provided ibuprofen, which helped relieve the pain slightly. I was also given fluoride mousse and a soothing gel for my teeth and lips to bring home for aftercare.

What truly touched me was the follow-upâ€”a WhatsApp message from the clinic the next day to check if I was feeling better. Their care and concern really stood out to me.

While the reaction and pain I experienced were likely due to my naturally sensitive teeth, I am still very pleased with the service provided. I highly recommend Asiaa Dental Clinic for their professionalism, warm service, and affordable pricing. The location is also relatively close to KSL (about 10mins walk), although do note that certain part of the clinic is currently undergoing renovation.

Thank you Dr Thasha and the team :)

5 Stars - Highly Recommend S Smilings Dental!

S Smilings Dental has never failed me since my very first visit about a year ago. Back then, I got stuck in a massive jam to JB and had to postpone my appointment last minute â€” they were so understanding and rescheduled it to a date that was super convenient for me without any hassle.

Just yesterday, they impressed me again. I needed a last-minute appointment for both my in-laws to get extractions done. Despite the short notice, they managed to slot in an afternoon session at 2:30pm for both of them â€” which was already amazing service.

We accidentally went to the wrong dental clinic and had to rush over to theirs, arriving slightly late around 2:45pm. Thankfully, the staff were patient and kind enough to wait for us. After a smooth registration process, the doctor promptly called in my in-laws one after the other with no long waiting time.

The extractions were done very fast and efficiently. Both my in-laws came out with no pain and big smiles â€” they were genuinely happy with the experience. That kind of care and professionalism is hard to come by.

I highly recommend S Smilings Dental to anyone looking for trustworthy, gentle, and accommodating dental care!

Thanks to my friend recommendation, I have an excellent experience in this dental clinic.

At first glance, I thought itâ€™s a â€˜normalâ€™ clinic but stepping in, I discovered the clinics is more like a mini Dental Center with a panel of dentist, each in their respective rooms to provide consultation.

Dr Fung is an amazing dentist! I had severe toothache and sensitivity for months, even after a filling. The pain spread to other teeth, making it hard to enjoy simple things like a warm beverage in the cold mornings or cold drinks after running out in the sun without the sensitivity or nagging fear at the back of my mind.

Dr Fung listened attentively to my concerns and explained all possible scenarios that gave me confidence that made me feel truly involved in my own care.

She performed a CBCT scan on-site, found cracks causing the pain, and diligently removed them. Now, I can drink hot and cold beverages pain-free.

Her expertise and genuine care about patiencesâ€™ well-being made all the differenceâ€”she not only fixed a piece of tooth but also a peace of mind.

Last but not least, the assistant at the counter was very professional and attentive, even arrange for cab service to my next destination!
